  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dbb \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0dc3\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0db8\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't play with fire, says China",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "China has warned the United States not to play with fire on the Taiwan issue after the United States approved the sale of military-technical assistance worth $108 million to Taiwan.",
        "The US Defense Cooperation Agency said in a statement on Friday that the State Department \"has made a decision to approve a foreign military equipment sale to the Office of the United States Economic and Cultural Representative in Taipei.\"",
        "This is the fifth arms sale to the Taiwan region since US President Joe Biden took office in January 2021, and is believed to be the fourth arms sale this year.",
        "China strongly opposes US arms sales to Taiwan and urges the US to cancel the arms sales plan, Foreign Ministry spokesman Wang Wenbin said at the press conference."
      ],
